New Records: Paul Stirling scored 88 from 92 balls, his finest ODI innings yet.
Jason Smith hit 91 from 93 balls, the highest score by a South African in this match.
Ireland's total of 284/9 was their highest score in the series.
Ireland won by 69 runs, their first victory in the series.
Key Match Events: South Africa collapsed to 10-3 in the first five overs, losing Ryan Rickelton, Reeza Hendricks, and Rassie van der Dussen.
Kyle Verreynne's 38-ball 38 was a late counterattack, but it ended in a dismissal.
Paul Stirling's dismissal of Mark Adair (4-0-12-2) and Graham Hume (2-32) were key moments in the Irish innings.
Jason Smith's partnership with Kyle Verreynne (23) was the only significant stand for South Africa.
Ireland's 179/3 after 15 overs set the platform for their victory.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was the third and final ODI of the series.
South Africa had already secured the series with wins by 139 and 174 runs in the first two matches.
Ireland's victory ended a disappointing tour with a 2-1 series loss to Afghanistan.
Others: The match was played at the Sheikh Zayed Stadium in Abu Dhabi.
Ireland's players included Paul Stirling (captain), Andrew Balbirnie, Curtis Campher, Harry Tector, and others.
South Africa's squad featured Ryan Rickelton, Reeza Hendricks, Rassie van der Dussen, and others.
